cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper proposes a framework for static cost analysis of parallel logic programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the challenges of predicting resource usage on parallel platforms, which relates to computer architecture (cs.AR). The analysis of cost equations/relations involves mathematical logic (cs.LO) and the paper proposes a method for solving cost relations, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper reports on an implementation within a system, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE).
